<h1 class="doc-page-title">Overlays</h1>

<p>
  By default the dropdown renders floating above the rest of your page but it doesn't
  prevent the user from clicking on anything other item. Overlays can fix that and makey
  dropdowns look cooler.
</p>

{{#code-sample hbs="overlays-1.hbs" as |partialName|}}
  {{partial partialName}}
{{/code-sample}}

<p>
  What do you have to know:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    By default overlays have a semitransparent back background, but you can change that
    using the <code>$ember-basic-dropdown-overlay-background</code> SASS variable or
    targeting the <code>.ember-basic-dropdown-overlay</code>
  </li>
  <li>
    By default the overlay has <code>pointer-events: none</code>, so it is transparent to
    clicks but you can change that using the <code>$ember-basic-dropdown-overlay-pointer-events</code>
    SASS variable or targeting the same class.
  </li>
</ul>

<p>
  In the next section we'll talk more how to customize the styles.
</p>

